---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 325 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Zest and halve @Sunkist® Blood Orange{1} and @Lemon{1}, keeping them separate. Thinly slice half the orange and half the lemon into rounds; stack rounds and cut into half-moons. (You'll use the rest of each later.) Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and finely diced).

> For 4 servings, dice the whole onion.

Pat @Steelhead Trout{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Place in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. Drizzle each fillet with @Olive Oil{5%tsp}, then rub with orange zest and @Garlic Powder{1%tsp}. Layer orange and lemon slices on top, then drizzle with more olive oil (about 1 TBSP per fillet).

> For 4 servings, use a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.

Roast on middle rack until trout is opaque and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Rice Pilaf ==

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup} to coat.

Add @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chive Crème Fraîche ==

Meanwhile, finely chop @Chives{1/4%oz}. Roughly chop @Pistachios{1/2%oz}. Peel and dice remaining orange.

> Place orange cut side down on a cutting board. Use a knife to easily remove the peel, then dice fruit.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Crème Fraîche{2%tbsp}, lemon zest, and half the chives. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Blood Orange Pistachio Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss @Arugula{2%oz}, diced orange, and pistachios with a large drizzle of olive oil and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice pilaf with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide pilaf and salad between plates. Top pilaf with trout; remove orange and lemon slices. Drizzle trout with chive crème fraîche. Sprinkle everything with remaining chives and serve.

> For a festive presentation, keep citrus slices on top of trout and serve with chive crème fraîche on the side. We don't recommend eating the citrus rind.